v:4 c:$ m:T03-quantize-notes role:dev x:audio/timing
gate: LOCKED

task: Add optional snap-to-grid quantization for locally played notes

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
out:
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/composables/useJamSession.ts
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/App.vue
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/components/JamControls.vue

depends: [T01-transport-controls, T02-metronome-sync]

context: |
  transport.quantize(beat, division) exists and is UNUSED. With a shared beat
  grid (T02) we can snap a played note's trigger time to the nearest subdivision
  so loose playing locks to the groove — and, crucially, so recorded loops
  (T04) land on clean grid positions (prerequisite for a capturable artifact).

  handleLocalNote (App.vue) currently triggers immediately. Quantize must delay
  the local trigger to the next quantized beat-time when enabled.

steps:
  1. useJamSession: add quantizeDivision ref (0 = off, else 1/2/4 = 1/4,1/8,1/16
     style snapping) + setter; return it.
  2. Provide a helper (composable or transport) that, given "now", returns the
     next quantized play time:
       nextQuantizedTime(division): number  // transport.now-based
     using transport.currentBeat + quantize() + beatToTime().
  3. App.vue handleLocalNote: when quantizeDivision > 0 and note is ON, schedule
     the local noteOn at the quantized time (use the engine's existing
     scheduleNoteOn against transport time, NOT immediate noteOn) and send the
     network note with that same intended time so peers align. When 0, keep
     current immediate behaviour.
  4. JamControls: add a small "Quantize" selector (Off / 1/4 / 1/8 / 1/16) in
     the Transport or Sound section, existing styles.

caution: |
  Quantizing adds intentional local latency (up to one grid step) — this is
  musically expected and must be OPT-IN (default Off) so it never fights the
  S03 min-latency work for players who want raw immediacy.

done:
  - Quantize Off (default) = current immediate behaviour, unchanged
  - Quantize 1/8 etc = local notes snap to grid and lock with the metronome
  - Peers receive the note timed to the same grid position
  - tsc --noEmit passes
